articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Chinese online retailer JD.com (9618.HK) said on Friday that it won a lawsuit against rival Alibaba (9988.HK), which was fined 1 billion yuan ($140.68 million) for monopolistic practices.
articles.title: JD.com wins antimonopoly lawsuit against Alibaba

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Activity in Russia's manufacturing sector expanded at its fastest pace in almost seven years in December, a business survey showed on Friday, though new export orders contracted for the second month running.
articles.title: Russian factory activity expands at fastest pace in seven years in Dec - PMI

articles.author: Jonathan Stempel
articles.description: Alphabet's Google (GOOGL.O) has agreed to settle a lawsuit claiming it secretly tracked the internet use of millions of people who thought they were doing their browsing privately.
articles.title: Google settles $5 billion consumer privacy lawsuit

articles.author: Sachin Ravikumar
articles.description: British house prices fell by 1.8% in the 12 months to December, recording the biggest decline over the course of a year since 2008 during the global financial crisis, mortgage lender Nationwide said on Friday.
articles.title: UK house prices fall in 2023, to stay subdued next year, says Nationwide

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: U.S. chipmaker Nvidia (NVDA.O) on Thursday launched a modified version of an advanced gaming chip designed to comply with U.S. export controls targeting China.
articles.title: Nvidia launches new gaming chip for China to comply with US export controls

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russia unleashed its largest drone and missile attack on Ukraine in months on Friday, killing 10 people and wounding at least 60 others in Kyiv, the south, west and east of the country, officials said.
articles.title: Russia launches massive air attack on Ukraine, at least 10 dead - Kyiv

articles.author: Andrew Goudsward
articles.description: Maine on Thursday disqualified Donald Trump from the state ballot in next year’s U.S. presidential primary election, becoming the second state to bar the former president for his role in the Jan. 6, 2021, attack on the U.S. Capitol.
articles.title: Maine elections official disqualifies Trump from presidential primary ballot

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: There's not much time to get over the New Year's partying: the most closely watched U.S. economic release and key euro area inflation data are on the calendar in the week ahead, suggesting a busy start to 2024.
articles.title: A quiet start to 2024? No way

articles.author: Rupam Jain
articles.description: Vishnu Dabad attributes his rise from poverty to powerful local politician to an animal: the cow.
articles.title: India's far-right cow vigilantes bolster clout before high-stake elections

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Arafat Barbakh
articles.description: Tens of thousands of newly displaced Gazans huddled under tarpaulins on Friday in the centre of the enclave after fleeing the latest offensive by Israeli tanks, while warplanes targeted the south, flattening homes and burying families as they slept.
articles.title: Displaced Gazans flee again as Israel launches fresh tank, air assaults
